        { q: "In the Horse, the Lateral Digital Extensor tendon inserts on the:", o: ["Extensor process of the 3rd Phalanx (Coffin bone)", "Proximal extremity of the 1st Phalanx (Long pastern)", "Middle Phalanx", "Navicular bone"], a: 1, e: "It does not reach the coffin bone like the common digital extensor." },
        { q: "The Flexor Carpi Radialis inserts primarily on the:", o: ["Accessory Carpal Bone", "Metacarpal Bone (Proximal end)", "Radius", "Olecranon"], a: 1, e: "It inserts on the proximal metacarpal region." },
        { q: "Which muscle is the primary extensor of the elbow joint?", o: ["Anconeus", "Triceps Brachii", "Biceps Brachii", "Brachialis"], a: 1, e: "The triceps brachii is the main extensor of the elbow." },
        { q: "The Rhomboid muscle in the Ox lacks which part compared to the Dog?", o: ["Cervical part", "Thoracic part", "Capitis part (Rhomboideus Capitis)", "None, all are present"], a: 2, e: "Rhomboideus capitis (to skull) is absent in ox/horse but present in dog/pig." },
        { q: "The Deep Pectoral muscle is also known as the:", o: ["Pectoralis Descendens", "Pectoralis Transversus", "Ascending Pectoral (Pectoralis Ascendens)", "Subclavius"], a: 2, e: "It ascends from sternum to brachial region." },
        { q: "The condition 'Capped Elbow' involves inflammation of the bursa over the:", o: ["Point of Shoulder", "Point of Elbow (Olecranon)", "Carpus", "Fetlock"], a: 1, e: "Bursitis over the olecranon tuber." },
        { q: "Which muscle lies in the Musculospiral Groove along with the Radial nerve?", o: ["Brachialis", "Coracobrachialis", "Biceps Brachii", "Triceps Brachii (Medial Head)"], a: 0, e: "The brachialis is intimately associated with the radial nerve here." },
        { q: "The Flexor Carpi Ulnaris inserts on the:", o: ["Metacarpal Tuberosity", "Accessory Carpal Bone", "Olecranon", "First Phalanx"], a: 1, e: "It primarily inserts on the accessory carpal bone." },
        { q: "In the Dog, the Supinator muscle acts to:", o: ["Rotate the paw laterally (palm up)", "Rotate the paw medially (palm down)", "Flex the elbow", "Extend the carpus only"], a: 0, e: "It supinates the paw (lateral rotation)." },
        { q: "The Teres Major muscle inserts on the Teres Tubercle of the Humerus along with the tendon of:", o: ["Latissimus Dorsi", "Subscapularis", "Coracobrachialis", "Deltoideus"], a: 0, e: "They share a common insertion site on the teres tuberosity." },
        { q: "The Manica Flexoria is a sleeve formed by the:", o: ["Deep Digital Flexor around the Superficial Digital Flexor", "Superficial Digital Flexor around the Deep Digital Flexor", "Suspensory Ligament around the Flexor tendons", "Check ligaments around the Carpus"], a: 1, e: "The SDFT splits and forms a sleeve around the DDFT at the fetlock." },
        { q: "The Extensor Carpi Obliquus is also known as:", o: ["Abductor Pollicis Longus", "Extensor Pollicis Longus", "Ulnaris Lateralis", "Pronator Teres"], a: 0, e: "It is the same as Abductor Pollicis Longus." },
        { q: "The main function of the Stay Apparatus in the horse is to:", o: ["Increase running speed", "Allow the horse to sleep while standing with minimal muscular effort", "Strengthen the kick", "Prevent over-flexion of the hoof"], a: 1, e: "Passive locking allows standing without constant muscle effort." },
        { q: "The Brachiocephalicus muscle is the principal:", o: ["Extensor of the elbow", "Protractor of the limb (advances the limb)", "Adductor of the limb", "Retractor of the limb"], a: 1, e: "It pulls the limb forward." },
        { q: "In the Ox, the Suspensory Ligament divides into:", o: ["Two branches", "Three branches", "Four branches (plus abaxial bands)", "It does not divide"], a: 2, e: "It must support two digits (III and IV), so it divides accordingly." },
        { q: "Which muscle fills the Supraspinous Fossa?", o: ["Infraspinatus", "Supraspinatus", "Subscapularis", "Rhomboideus"], a: 1, e: "Supraspinatus occupies the supraspinous fossa." },
        { q: "The Capsularis muscle (Articularis Humeri) is found in the:", o: ["Ox", "Horse", "Dog", "Pig"], a: 1, e: "Small muscle in the horse preventing capsule pinching." },
        { q: "The Tensor Fasciae Antebrachii acts to:", o: ["Flex the elbow", "Extend the elbow and tense the forearm fascia", "Flex the carpus", "Supinate the forearm"], a: 1, e: "It assists the triceps and tenses the fascia." },
        { q: "Which head of the Triceps originates from the humerus (not the scapula)?", o: ["Long Head", "Lateral Head", "Both Lateral and Medial Heads", "None"], a: 2, e: "Only the long head arises from the scapula; lateral and medial arise from the humerus." },
        { q: "The Common Digital Extensor inserts on the:", o: ["Extensor process of the Distal Phalanx (P3)", "Proximal Phalanx (P1)", "Middle Phalanx (P2)", "Navicular Bone"], a: 0, e: "It attaches to the extensor process of P3." },
        { q: "The Subclavius muscle is well developed in the:", o: ["Dog", "Horse", "Ox", "Cat"], a: 1, e: "The horse has a well-developed subclavius forming the cranial pectoral girdle." }
